			<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leezer</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Dr Friend</p>
          <p rend="indent(5)">It was indeed<lb/> with great regret that I passed through<lb/> your city without the pleasure of seeing you.<lb/> As it always affords me a great Satisfaction to<lb/> see you.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">My great object in writing to you<lb/> is to ask a particular favour which you<lb/> are both able &#38; I hope willing to execute.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">In your last No. on the last<lb/> page you have an advertisement of a Jewish<lb/> Lady in the vicinity of <placeName>Phila.</placeName> willing to<lb/> take a few Young Ladies for &#36;200.<hi rend="sup">00</hi>&#47;<hi rend="sub">100</hi> per year<lb/> for Boarding &#38; Education.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Is she capable of<lb/> instructing young girls for twelve to fourteen<lb/> years of age who are far advanced in English<lb/> &#38; Music and is she able to give them<lb/> instructions in French.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">The person wishing to<lb/> place his daughters under her care will much<lb/> depend on your judgement in every respect&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Your attention and prompt answer<lb/> will much oblige</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)">Yours &#38;c</p>
			<p><placeName>Cinc</placeName> <date>Apl 10<hi rend="sup">th</hi> &#47; 48</date></p>
          <p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Elias Mayer</persName></p>
          
